      "content": "July 15, 1870\n\nToday, I witnessed yet another demonstration of the \"uncivilized\" nature of our Indian subjects. The natives gathered in the streets, their faces painted in grotesque patterns, their cries echoing through the air. It is clear that without our guidance, they would remain in perpetual chaos. We have a moral duty to bring order and civilization to these people, to civilize them with our superior ways. They may resist at first, but in time, they will come to see the wisdom of British rule. Our presence here is not merely for exploitation, but for the betterment of these \"savages.\" We are the harbingers of progress, and their gratitude will be evident in the years to come.",
